Army chief Bipin Rawat lauds force for work during cyclone Vardah 
10-3-2017 
Army Chief General Bipin Rawat Army Chief General Bipin Rawat

Army Chief General Bipin Rawat on Friday appreciated the force for the “good work” done by it during the December 2016 cyclone ‘Vardah’. He lauded the army personnel during his visit to the Headquarters Dakshin Bharat Area here. Rawat was briefed on the assistance provided by the Army during the Vardha Cyclone and the rescue and relief operations undertaken by it, a Defence release said.

Watch What Else Is Making News

“General Bipin Rawat appreciated the good work done by the Army during Vardah cyclone and expressed satisfaction on the welfare initiatives being undertaken by the Formation,” it said.

Cyclone Vardah had made landfall here on December 12, 2106, severely affecting the northern districts of Chennai, Tiruvallur and Kancheepuram.

The Army chief was on a two-day visit here on March 9 and 10, the release said.

He was received by Lieutenant General RK Anand, General Officer Commanding, Dakshin Bharat Area who briefed him about the training activities being carried out at various Regimental Centres.

Rawat was also briefed on various welfare measures being undertaken for serving and retired army personnel of the five southern states of Telangana, Andhra Pradesh, Tamil Nadu, Karnataka and Kerala, it said. 
